-- Venezuela Sends Units of Soldiers to Border With Colombia, Chavez Says
-- Jose Orozco
-- 2010-07-31T01:11:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/venezuela-sends-units-of-soldiers-to-border-with-colombia-chavez-says.html

          
          
             Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez 
said military troops had been sent to the border with Colombia
as a preventive measure against an attack from neighboring
Colombia.  
 Chavez also said a Colombian helicopter entered Venezuelan
territory for a few minutes. He spoke in comments carried by
state television and did not give additional details..  
